                <head>244. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>In a letter of June 5, President <persName>Eisenhower</persName> replied to
                    President <persName corresp="#p_KODJ1">Kubitschek</persName>’s letter of May 28.
                        <persName>Eisenhower</persName> suggested consultations between the two
                    governments before they approached the other American Republics on matters
                    affecting common interests and welfare. Assistant Secretary of State <persName
                        corresp="#p_RRRJ1">Rubottom</persName> delivered President
                        <persName>Eisenhower</persName>’s letter to President <persName
                        corresp="#p_KODJ1">Kubitschek</persName> in Rio de Janeiro on June 10. For
                    texts of the letters, see <hi rend="italic">Public Papers of the Presidents of
                        the United States: <persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Dwight D.
                            Eisenhower</persName>, 1958,</hi> page 463.</p>
            </div>
